      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, i need some help. I'm an HR manager at a tech firm in Austin and we have a candidate who made it all the way to the final round for a senior dev role, but we decided to go with someone else. They were actually really strong, especially with their backend experience, but just wasn't the perfect fit for our current stack. Can you help me draft a rejection email that is professional but still kind since they put in so much time?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Hello, I am an HR manager at a tech firm in Austin and we have a candidate who made it all the way to the final round for a senior dev role, but we decided to go with someone else. They were actually really strong, especially with their backend experience, but just wasn't the perfect fit for our current stack. Can you help me draft a rejection email that is professional but still kind since they put in so much time?\n\nHere is a draft for your rejection email, which I hope you find helpful.\n\n**Subject:** Update on Your Application – Senior Developer Role\n\nDear [Candidate Name],\n\nThank you for taking the time to interview with us and for your impressive contributions during the final round. We were genuinely impressed by your deep backend experience and the strong technical skills you demonstrated.\n\nAfter careful consideration, we have decided to move forward with another candidate whose background aligns more closely with our current tech stack and immediate project needs. This was not an easy decision, as we know you are a talented developer, and we appreciate the energy and effort you brought to our process.\n\nWe wish you the very best in your job search and hope our paths cross again in the future.\n\nWarmly,\n\n[Your Name",
